DataElement.preferredDefinition: A unique identifier assigned to a ClinicalTrials.gov clinical study.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: A Web-based resource that provides patients, their family members, health care professionals, researchers, and the public with access to information on publicly and privately supported clinical studies. A service of the National Institutes of Health (NIH), ClinicalTrials.gov is both a registry and a results database._Research conducted with human subjects or on material of human origin in which an investigator directly interacts with human subjects; includes development of new technologies, study of mechanisms of human diseases, therapy, clinical trials, epidemiologic, behavior, and health services research.

RepresentationTerm.preferredDefinition: A formal document that describes a complete plan of research activity in the framework of a clinical study; specifically, the study objective(s), design, methodology, eligibility requests for prospective subjects and controls; intervention regimen(s), proposed methods of analysis of data; statistical considerations, and organization of the study. The protocol usually also provides the background and rationale for the trial, but these could be represented in other protocol referenced documents.:One or more characters used to identify, name, or characterize the nature, properties, or contents of a thing.
